# Styling Rules

## PrimeVue Component Styling
- All PrimeVue components should follow these styling rules:
  1. Use custom classes for consistent styling
  2. Follow the established color scheme
  3. Maintain responsive design patterns

## Button Styles
- Button classes should follow these patterns:
  ```css
  .p-button {
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 12px;
  }
  ```

## Form Field Styles
- Form fields should use these base styles:
  ```css
  .p-iftalabel {
    label {
      top: -0.375rem;
      background-color: white;
      font-size: 0.625rem;
      color: #999999;
    }
  }
  ```

## Modal and Dialog Styles
- Modal components should use:
  ```css
  .custom-dialog-full {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0.5rem 0.5rem 0 0;
  }
  ```

## Layout Components
- Layout components should follow these patterns:
  1. Use Tailwind utility classes for spacing
  2. Follow mobile-first responsive design
  3. Use consistent padding and margin values

## Color Scheme
- Use these color variables:
  ```css
  :root {
    --p-primary-600: #00AEF2;
    --p-gray-900: #111827;
    --p-gray-200: #E5E7EB;
  }
  ```
